WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.804 --> 00:00:13.814
.

2
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:21.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

3
00:01:03.864 --> 00:01:05.996
911. What's your emergency?

4
00:01:06.957 --> 00:01:08.118
Hello?

5
00:01:10.291 --> 00:01:12.253
This is 911. Go ahead.

6
00:01:13.414 --> 00:01:16.877
This is Suh Young-chul. who used to work at Chains Bio.

7
00:01:17.718 --> 00:01:22.012
Today at the Doongwoori Building I plan to run an experiment.

8
00:01:22.383 --> 00:01:25.095
Excuse me? Can you repeat that. please?

9
00:01:25.135 --> 00:01:27.428
Ah. not an experiment.

10
00:01:27.728 --> 00:01:29.139
It's closer to terrorism.

11
00:01:29.310 --> 00:01:30.141
What?

12
00:01:30.271 --> 00:01:35.146
That's right. A highly contagious bioterror attack.

13
00:01:38.819 --> 00:01:41.652
I tested the pathogen in my body.

14
00:01:48.199 --> 00:01:50.161
And it was a success.

15
00:01:51.582 --> 00:01:55.706
I am the only vaccine that can stop this outbreak.

16
00:01:59.170 --> 00:02:01.172
Organisms of the same species that.

17
00:02:01.212 --> 00:02:03.424
for a certain time. live in the same place

18
00:02:17.728 --> 00:02:19.320
Why are you waiting for me?

19
00:02:20.781 --> 00:02:23.484
You're 10 minutes late. What was it this time?

20
00:02:24.485 --> 00:02:25.786
It was nothing.

21
00:02:25.906 --> 00:02:26.657
Traffic was bad.

22
00:02:26.737 --> 00:02:29.079
so the taxi driver tried to let me off across the street.

23
00:02:29.540 --> 00:02:29.870
So ?

24
00:02:31.121 --> 00:02:33.244
Yeah. these things happen.

25
00:02:34.124 --> 00:02:37.378
It's okay if I say it. but how can he say that to me?

26
00:02:37.418 --> 00:02:38.499
So ?

27
00:02:40.631 --> 00:02:42.052
It's not what I wanted.

28
00:02:42.303 --> 00:02:44.004
I said. however long it takes.

29
00:02:44.054 --> 00:02:45.926
drop me off at the spot I chose.

30
00:02:50.511 --> 00:02:51.472
What?

31
00:02:52.263 --> 00:02:54.104
So it's my fault again?

32
00:02:54.355 --> 00:02:56.477
Welcome to the Chains Bio Conference.

33
00:02:56.477 --> 00:02:58.899
a leading platform for future technology.

34
00:02:58.939 --> 00:02:59.980
Thank you.

35
00:03:00.441 --> 00:03:02.363
You brought the invitation I gave you?

36
00:03:02.823 --> 00:03:05.776
...and now we'll hear from CEO Kang Woo-cheol.

37
00:03:05.826 --> 00:03:07.658
Please give him a round of applause.

38
00:03:13.744 --> 00:03:14.625
Is that the guy?

39
00:03:14.625 --> 00:03:17.248
The one I should grovel to if I want to work here?

40
00:03:18.419 --> 00:03:21.041
If only you got along with your dean.

41
00:03:21.041 --> 00:03:23.043
this wouldn't be necessary.

42
00:03:24.004 --> 00:03:26.427
Sure. my fault again.

43
00:03:27.348 --> 00:03:29.099
But don't you care how that dean

44
00:03:29.099 --> 00:03:30.761
treated his graduate students?

45
00:03:30.761 --> 00:03:32.183
No. I don't.

46
00:03:32.603 --> 00:03:35.055
Well. I'm sure he's a jerk.

47
00:03:35.306 --> 00:03:37.188
And you couldn't tolerate that.

48
00:03:37.858 --> 00:03:40.271
So you got on his bad side. and didn't get reappointed.

49
00:03:43.113 --> 00:03:45.115
I'm just curious...

50
00:03:45.616 --> 00:03:47.908
Why are you so fixated on your ex-wife's career

51
00:03:47.908 --> 00:03:49.280
10 years after the divorce?

52
00:03:51.071 --> 00:03:52.743
Because you have no friends.

53
00:03:53.494 --> 00:03:56.377
You keep doing things that make people hate you.

54
00:03:56.377 --> 00:03:58.829
Does your wife know you look after your ex-wife like this?

55
00:03:58.829 --> 00:04:02.383
My wife is not as sensitive as you are.

56
00:04:02.883 --> 00:04:04.965
She's probably even concerned for you.

57
00:04:05.676 --> 00:04:06.927
What a cool wife.

58
00:04:07.508 --> 00:04:10.261
You're a great match. I'm happy for you.

59
00:04:10.431 --> 00:04:13.013
If I say our company's main business

60
00:04:13.013 --> 00:04:15.015
is collective intelligence.

61
00:04:15.015 --> 00:04:16.517
people might wonder.

62
00:04:16.647 --> 00:04:18.058
"Why is a bio company.

63
00:04:18.058 --> 00:04:21.232
rather than an IT company. studying that topic?"

64
00:04:21.732 --> 00:04:24.405
Collective intelligence is a common term

65
00:04:24.405 --> 00:04:26.237
in the field of sociology.

66
00:04:26.407 --> 00:04:29.410
but the first person to use the term

67
00:04:29.570 --> 00:04:32.413
was an entomologist who studied ants.

68
00:04:32.453 --> 00:04:34.285
William Morton Wheeler.

69
00:04:34.575 --> 00:04:37.828
Collective intelligence is a key force driving evolution.

70
00:04:38.169 --> 00:04:41.332
You know the yellow slime mold 'Physarum polycephalum'?

71
00:04:41.752 --> 00:04:43.424
These fellows upgrade themselves

72
00:04:43.424 --> 00:04:44.925
through information exchange

73
00:04:44.925 --> 00:04:48.128
and optimize the direction of their growth towards food.

74
00:04:48.629 --> 00:04:50.631
Although not multicellular organisms.

75
00:04:50.631 --> 00:04:52.223
they can learn and remember.

76
00:04:52.683 --> 00:04:55.226
Inspired by these remarkable traits.

77
00:04:55.226 --> 00:04:56.977
we were able to dramatically improve

78
00:04:57.017 --> 00:04:59.059
the production of organic semiconductors.

79
00:04:59.480 --> 00:05:02.062
Let's give a hand to our little collaborators.

80
00:05:06.106 --> 00:05:08.609
This guy's more interesting than I expected.

81
00:05:08.859 --> 00:05:11.702
This isn't some lame company that makes copycat drugs.

82
00:05:11.822 --> 00:05:13.824
It's a serious. enterprising firm.

83
00:05:14.155 --> 00:05:15.656
After I introduced you.

84
00:05:15.656 --> 00:05:17.868
they even sent another invitation for you.

85
00:05:18.869 --> 00:05:21.001
Actually. that's why I came.

86
00:05:21.582 --> 00:05:24.295
I was curious what this message meant.

87
00:05:24.465 --> 00:05:26.377
To Prof. Kwon: Imperfect communication.

88
00:05:26.417 --> 00:05:27.668
the source of all tragedy

89
00:05:27.718 --> 00:05:31.011
...so this chip helps damaged nerves carry information.

90
00:05:31.172 --> 00:05:34.765
We injected it into a rat with severed spinal nerves

91
00:05:34.805 --> 00:05:36.557
and paralyzed hind legs.

92
00:05:37.137 --> 00:05:40.351
and as you can see. just a moment later.

93
00:05:40.811 --> 00:05:43.984
It was able to move no different from a healthy rat.

94
00:05:51.242 --> 00:05:53.244
If we continue with this research.

95
00:05:53.244 --> 00:05:55.576
and apply it to the human brain.

96
00:05:55.786 --> 00:05:58.909
I believe it may enable a direct transfer

97
00:05:58.949 --> 00:06:01.702
of information between individuals.

98
00:06:02.793 --> 00:06:04.124
When that happens.

99
00:06:04.505 --> 00:06:06.297
we may live in a world where

100
00:06:06.337 --> 00:06:09.510
you can't think bad thoughts in front of others.

101
00:06:11.051 --> 00:06:12.923
Thank you. CEO Kang.

102
00:06:13.093 --> 00:06:15.556
Please give him a round of applause!

103
00:06:23.103 --> 00:06:25.526
Next. to introduce Chains Bio's global market strategy...

104
00:06:32.863 --> 00:06:34.825
It's your first vacation in ages.

105
00:06:35.156 --> 00:06:38.699
So why spend it with the younger brother you see every day?

106
00:06:38.789 --> 00:06:43.043
This way I can get some fresh air. go shopping...

107
00:06:43.043 --> 00:06:45.456
You know how stifling it is working at a computer all day?

108
00:06:50.461 --> 00:06:54.094
Wow. look at all the camping stuff they have these days.

109
00:06:54.305 --> 00:06:55.886
I could just live outdoors.

110
00:06:57.137 --> 00:06:58.599
The clothes are nice. too.

111
00:07:00.601 --> 00:07:02.893
Should we go camping? On your next vacation?

112
00:07:03.564 --> 00:07:05.976
-The two of us? - Yeah. let's go.

113
00:07:06.267 --> 00:07:07.608
We'll grill some meat...

114
00:07:07.688 --> 00:07:09.360
That'd be great!

115
00:07:09.860 --> 00:07:11.482
We can go. why not?

116
00:07:11.482 --> 00:07:14.074
That's great. I'll buy some equipment.

117
00:07:14.825 --> 00:07:17.198
You get back to work. Lunchtime will end soon.

118
00:07:17.198 --> 00:07:20.030
- No. I'll head back after you. - No need.

119
00:07:20.030 --> 00:07:22.743
The facilities here are great. So convenient.

120
00:07:23.454 --> 00:07:27.918
Don't I work my ass off so I can live in civilization?

121
00:07:27.918 --> 00:07:30.171
You always go on about civilization.

122
00:07:30.171 --> 00:07:32.092
why do you want to go camping?

123
00:07:32.092 --> 00:07:33.754
Camping is civilization. too.

124
00:07:33.964 --> 00:07:35.886
Go on. See you at home.

125
00:07:36.177 --> 00:07:37.718
I'll look around before going.

126
00:07:39.139 --> 00:07:39.760
Okay. bye...

127
00:07:39.760 --> 00:07:39.970
-Take care..- Yeah.

128
00:07:41.262 --> 00:07:41.512
Take care. Yeah.

129
00:07:45.226 --> 00:07:48.018
Hello. sir. I enjoyed your presentation.

130
00:07:48.149 --> 00:07:49.730
Oh. Professor Han.

131
00:07:49.940 --> 00:07:53.314
This is Professor Kwon Se-jeong. who I mentioned last time.

132
00:07:53.564 --> 00:07:55.115
Thank you for inviting me.

133
00:07:55.156 --> 00:07:57.738
And for this note on my invitation.

134
00:07:58.699 --> 00:07:59.950
Just a moment.

135
00:08:00.821 --> 00:08:01.872
Hello?

136
00:08:02.032 --> 00:08:03.123
Mr. Kang Woo-cheol?

137
00:08:03.624 --> 00:08:05.376
Yes. Who's speaking?

138
00:08:05.416 --> 00:08:08.169
I'm Lee Bong-seok. from the Seoul Counterterrorism Squad.

139
00:08:08.289 --> 00:08:09.580
How can I help you?

140
00:08:09.750 --> 00:08:11.462
You know a man named Suh Young-chul?

141
00:08:12.213 --> 00:08:14.885
This call seems important. Let's talk later.

142
00:08:14.885 --> 00:08:16.967
Ah. sure. We'll wait.

143
00:08:20.511 --> 00:08:22.643
You sure he's the one who sent this invitation?

144
00:08:22.683 --> 00:08:24.475
What are you doing? Go after him.

145
00:08:24.685 --> 00:08:25.186
What?

146
00:08:25.186 --> 00:08:26.977
Just hand him your card

147
00:08:27.017 --> 00:08:30.271
and say "I'm Kwon Se-jeong." that's all. .

148
00:08:38.529 --> 00:08:40.741
Why are you looking for Dr. Suh?

149
00:08:40.991 --> 00:08:41.992
We received a call

150
00:08:41.992 --> 00:08:44.285
that Dr. Suh is planning a terrorist attack

151
00:08:44.285 --> 00:08:46.497
in the building hosting your conference.

152
00:08:49.170 --> 00:08:51.172
I think I saw him today at the conference.

153
00:08:51.332 --> 00:08:52.333
Are you certain?

154
00:08:53.043 --> 00:08:54.425
Not 100% certain.

155
00:08:54.675 --> 00:08:56.177
He was standing too far away.

156
00:08:56.377 --> 00:08:58.759
Our team will arrive there soon.

157
00:08:58.759 --> 00:09:01.011
If you see him again. call me immediately at this number.

158
00:09:01.011 --> 00:09:02.383
All right. I will.

159
00:09:28.159 --> 00:09:29.830
Nice speech. Woo-cheol.

160
00:09:30.251 --> 00:09:31.542
So impressive.

161
00:09:32.413 --> 00:09:34.545
Information exchange through organic semiconductors?

162
00:09:35.376 --> 00:09:39.300
You know how hard I researched that.

163
00:09:40.421 --> 00:09:42.803
Consciousness in a multilateral network.

164
00:09:43.384 --> 00:09:46.227
Well. if that existed.

165
00:09:46.807 --> 00:09:49.850
no one would be betrayed and kicked out like me. right?

166
00:09:50.311 --> 00:09:51.562
You freak.

167
00:09:52.933 --> 00:09:56.277
The technology you researched can't be used anywhere.

168
00:09:57.778 --> 00:09:58.609
Bro.

169
00:09:59.400 --> 00:10:02.693
I'm taking humanity to the next level.

170
00:10:04.155 --> 00:10:06.657
Enabling a second cognitive revolution.

171
00:10:11.872 --> 00:10:13.043
You know what?

172
00:10:13.584 --> 00:10:14.755
You...

173
00:10:15.956 --> 00:10:17.708
are just a psycho.

174
00:10:18.259 --> 00:10:20.341
Get lost. you loser!

175
00:10:25.426 --> 00:10:27.218
But when you hired me.

176
00:10:27.678 --> 00:10:30.060
you said my research was great.

177
00:10:30.221 --> 00:10:32.313
That you respected my research.

178
00:10:33.354 --> 00:10:37.438
It was all just an act. so you could steal my research.

179
00:10:38.439 --> 00:10:40.191
And now... psycho?

180
00:10:41.031 --> 00:10:43.364
You stole research from that psycho.

181
00:10:44.735 --> 00:10:48.659
You just want to make humans go extinct. don't you?

182
00:10:49.620 --> 00:10:51.292
Not extinct.

183
00:10:51.412 --> 00:10:52.743
It's a birth.

184
00:10:53.164 --> 00:10:54.745
The birth of a new humanity.

185
00:10:55.166 --> 00:10:56.707
Just imagine it.

186
00:10:56.917 --> 00:10:59.380
Perfect communication will be possible.

187
00:10:59.670 --> 00:11:02.213
All the byproducts of crass individualism.

188
00:11:02.253 --> 00:11:04.215
jealousy. rivalry. suspicion...

189
00:11:05.886 --> 00:11:09.430
Those bizarre losses that arise from unstable communication.

190
00:11:09.760 --> 00:11:11.642
That's what I'm trying to stop.

191
00:11:15.146 --> 00:11:16.187
Wow!

192
00:11:19.520 --> 00:11:21.572
You crazy freak.

193
00:11:23.324 --> 00:11:24.405
Give it a try.

194
00:11:24.695 --> 00:11:26.116
It's got nothing to do with me.

195
00:11:26.527 --> 00:11:29.200
I'm clocking out. so good luck with that.

196
00:11:30.991 --> 00:11:35.376
I want you to be the link between me and the new humanity.

197
00:11:42.293 --> 00:11:43.384
What the hell are you doing?

198
00:11:43.714 --> 00:11:44.675
Research.

199
00:11:44.715 --> 00:11:46.046
You goddamned maniac!

200
00:12:28.008 --> 00:12:29.220
Hey. look at this.

201
00:12:29.680 --> 00:12:30.721
Hey mister!

202
00:12:30.801 --> 00:12:32.303
Shouldn't we call 911?

203
00:12:51.492 --> 00:12:52.493
Did you talk to him?

204
00:12:55.115 --> 00:12:56.457
Seemed like a bad time.

205
00:12:56.457 --> 00:12:58.459
Really? Just a sec.

206
00:13:00.541 --> 00:13:03.294
No. really. I don't think he'll want to talk now.

207
00:13:09.840 --> 00:13:12.303
Let's go eat. He'll call back.

208
00:13:24.945 --> 00:13:27.107
Police. Where's the conference hall?

209
00:13:27.238 --> 00:13:29.740
Turn left and go up the stairs. then...

210
00:13:34.745 --> 00:13:35.706
What is that?

211
00:13:39.710 --> 00:13:40.541
Go.

212
00:13:41.752 --> 00:13:43.254
Sir. are you okay?

213
00:13:49.340 --> 00:13:50.721
Call the containment team. - What?

214
00:13:50.721 --> 00:13:52.052
Call for a lockdown!

215
00:14:01.061 --> 00:14:01.732
Hi!

216
00:14:01.732 --> 00:14:04.235
Where are you. Daddy? What are you doing?

217
00:14:04.395 --> 00:14:06.066
I'll head home now.

218
00:14:06.187 --> 00:14:08.529
Honey. where's your passport?

219
00:14:08.649 --> 00:14:10.901
Should be in the drawer in the study.

220
00:14:12.032 --> 00:14:14.575
- You still with Professor Kwon? - Yeah.

221
00:14:14.575 --> 00:14:16.036
I'll head home soon.

222
00:14:16.537 --> 00:14:17.538
Want to say hi?

223
00:14:21.081 --> 00:14:23.003
Anyway. hurry home. We need to pack.

224
00:14:23.164 --> 00:14:23.874
Okay.

225
00:14:23.874 --> 00:14:26.507
Say bye to Dad. - Hurry home. Dad!

226
00:14:27.918 --> 00:14:29.420
Where are you going? Traveling?

227
00:14:33.514 --> 00:14:36.177
Why don't you answer? You immigrating or something?

228
00:14:36.717 --> 00:14:38.098
Well...

229
00:14:38.639 --> 00:14:41.182
A teaching position opened at UC Irvine...

230
00:14:41.432 --> 00:14:44.475
Really. you're going to the US? For how long?

231
00:14:45.226 --> 00:14:47.858
This time. we may just stay there.

232
00:14:54.825 --> 00:14:57.448
Ah. now I get it.

233
00:14:58.078 --> 00:15:00.120
You're leaving. so you wanted to set

234
00:15:00.161 --> 00:15:02.493
your ex-wife up with a job before going?

235
00:15:03.454 --> 00:15:04.705
Anyway. congrats.

236
00:15:04.835 --> 00:15:06.457
It's good news. right?

237
00:15:09.710 --> 00:15:12.132
Since it's the last time. let me ask.

238
00:15:13.424 --> 00:15:15.386
Why did you marry me?

239
00:15:18.969 --> 00:15:20.561
Well...

240
00:15:21.432 --> 00:15:24.975
The way you never back down when you think you're right...

241
00:15:24.975 --> 00:15:26.607
your personality?

242
00:15:26.767 --> 00:15:30.321
Wow. after you always begged me not to do that.

243
00:15:30.571 --> 00:15:31.942
You liked that?

244
00:15:33.364 --> 00:15:36.157
I did... I liked it.

245
00:15:37.158 --> 00:15:38.909
But I couldn't keep up with you.

246
00:15:39.280 --> 00:15:41.332
I couldn't handle it.

247
00:15:41.782 --> 00:15:44.535
I've always been a bit of a coward.

248
00:15:45.956 --> 00:15:48.169
That's why I broke up with you.

249
00:15:51.842 --> 00:15:54.545
Don't worry. I'll be okay.

250
00:15:55.676 --> 00:15:58.299
It's not like you. talking like that.

251
00:15:59.350 --> 00:16:00.681
I'm not saying you should change...

252
00:16:00.681 --> 00:16:01.762
Done eating?

253
00:16:02.102 --> 00:16:04.555
Let's go. your wife is waiting.

254
00:16:05.356 --> 00:16:07.017
There she goes again....

255
00:16:11.562 --> 00:16:12.563
Thank you.

256
00:16:14.365 --> 00:16:15.986
Have a good evening.

257
00:16:17.738 --> 00:16:18.989
Welcome.

258
00:16:19.200 --> 00:16:20.951
Shit. that's so funny. Yeah...

259
00:16:22.373 --> 00:16:23.914
Hey. I'll call you back.

260
00:16:24.124 --> 00:16:25.826
I'm gonna stuff my face.

261
00:16:26.247 --> 00:16:26.917
Yeah.

262
00:16:29.500 --> 00:16:31.292
Three people? - Yes. three.

263
00:16:31.462 --> 00:16:35.256
From here to here....we'll take it all.

264
00:16:35.756 --> 00:16:36.387
All of it?

265
00:16:36.757 --> 00:16:37.968
Yeah. all of it.

266
00:16:43.264 --> 00:16:45.266
You're paying today.

267
00:16:46.307 --> 00:16:46.937
Got it?

268
00:16:50.521 --> 00:16:52.443
Damn it. So-eun!

269
00:16:53.274 --> 00:16:55.486
You should answer him. huh?

270
00:16:59.740 --> 00:17:01.862
The entire building is being locked down.

271
00:17:02.032 --> 00:17:04.745
Security personnel. evacuate everyone immediately!

272
00:17:06.076 --> 00:17:06.787
What's going on?

273
00:17:10.621 --> 00:17:11.502
Hey!

274
00:17:19.840 --> 00:17:20.631
Everyone evacuate!

275
00:17:20.681 --> 00:17:22.343
Move! Out of the way!

276
00:17:25.686 --> 00:17:28.729
Come out! Everyone move!

277
00:17:37.318 --> 00:17:39.400
Isn't the parking lot that way?

278
00:17:39.530 --> 00:17:40.611
Se-jeong.

279
